value.snippet: Its exact length varied from place to place but was roughly between 1.9 and 2.1 metres (6 ft 3 in and 6 ft 11 in). Elle (ell) [ edit] Distance between elbow and fingertip. In the North, often 2 feet, In Prussia 17⁄8 feet, in the South variable, often 21⁄2 feet. The smallest known German Elle is 402.8 mm (15.86 in ), the longest 811 mm (31.9 in).

value.name: 3 Ways to Calculate Cubic Inches - wikiHow
value.snippet: To calculate cubic inches, start by measuring the length, width, and depth of the box you're measuring in inches. Then, multiply the length by the width. Finally, multiply the product of the length and the width by the depth of the box to find the volume in cubic inches.

value.name: Cubic Inches Calculator - Calculatorway
value.snippet: Cubic inches are a unit for measuring the volume of a shape. A cubic inch is the volume of a block with each side 1 inch in length. This means that a cubic inch is the volume of a box that is 1 inch by 1 inch by 1 inch. For example, a box that is 1 inch by 1 inch by 2 inches would have a volume of 2 cubic inches.

value.name: Zoll (Pre-metric Prussian) | Units of Measurement Wiki | Fandom
value.snippet: The Zoll (generally rendered inch in English) was a Prussian unit of length or distance prior to 1872, when the German Empire was formed, and all traditional local systems were abolished in Germany. value.name: Cubic inches - Math
value.snippet: 1 cubic inch = 16.387 milliliters Since so many different units of volume are used, it is important to be able to convert between them. Example The Cadillac Series 353 had a 353 cubic inch engine. What is its engine displacement in liters (L)? There are 61.024 in 3 in 1 L, so dividing 353 by 61.024 will yield the engine displacement in in 3.
